<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.207984>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Chlamydolecanium conchioides Goux; adult female. Where: A = dorsal preopercular pore; B = dorsal simple pore; C = dorsal microduct; D = anal plates; E 1 and E 2 = marginal setae; F = marginal simple pore; G = marginal microduct; H = pregenital disc-pore; I = spiracular disc-pore; J = ventral microduct; K = ventral tubular ducts; L 1 and L 2 = ventral setae; M = antenna, and N = tarsus and claw detail." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/207984/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.207985>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Chlamydolecanium conchioides Goux; young teneral female. Letters refer to the same structures as Figure 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/207985/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.207986>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Chlamydolecanium conchioides Goux; first-instar nymph. Where: A = dorsal simple pore; B = detail of anal plates; C 1, C 2 and C 3 = marginal setae; D = dermal spinules; E = spiracular disc-pore; F = ventral microduct; G = antenna; H = tarsus + claw detail." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/207986/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

